            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "The real project is much more complex with a number of other files in these directories.  The entire project is built by CMake and the full target has Fortran and C source/header files associated with it, so we generally need these directories to be `include_directories` for the target.  This results in the include path for the Cython compilation, which I agree is unnecessary but as far as I can tell it should not be invalid.\n\nI don't think I fully understand your comment about \"mixing different sub-directories\".  Can you elaborate a bit?  I agree that a local import should just work, but I thought that is what we were doing.\n\nI don't understand why Cython is even looking for a pxd file by that name.  And this only happens if the module file is pure Python and has the same name as the package.  If there is something actually wrong with what we are doing, please help me understand what we should be doing differently.",
