            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> mixing different sub-directories\n\nIf I understand correctly, you have a package called `CythonTest` and a module inside of it called `CythonTest.py`. Then, as include path, you do not set the base directory but the package directory (`CythonTest`), so Cython would now base its search in the project root directory and in the package directory, a subdirectory, which leads to overlapping search paths. The include directory lacks the package part of the module paths. That's the confusing part.",
